        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:59PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Newnan, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Newnan, Grantville, Moreland, Sharpsburg, Turin, East Newnan, Dunaway
Gardens, Arnco-Sargent, Thomas Crossroads, Handy, Madras, and Plant
Yates.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
